==English==
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''combinatoriality'''
#{{music}} a [[transformation]] or [[operation]] such as transposition or transposed [[inversion]] that maps the [[complement]] of a [[set]] of [[pitch class]]es, most commonly done with [[hexachord]]s (DeLone et. al. (Eds.), 1975, chap. 6).

